00:13:56.240 --> 00:14:00.240
and successfully completed Jerusalem walls.

00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:03.240
But what further challenges lay ahead of them?

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:09.240
We now invite you to watch the drama stirring conclusion, Nehemiah.

00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:13.240
The joy of Jehovah is your stronghold, part two.

00:14:13.240 --> 00:14:31.639
It was now Tishrae, the start of a month-long festival.

00:14:31.639 --> 00:14:37.919
He had just rebuilt the wall of Jehovah's Great City.

00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:44.919
Now, it was time to rebuild the spirituality of his chosen people.

00:14:44.919 --> 00:14:46.919
Many did not know God's law.

00:14:46.919 --> 00:14:55.419
Who better to help us gain understanding than a man who had come before me, Ezra?

00:14:55.419 --> 00:15:00.830
The regulations and judicial decisions of Jehovah.

00:15:00.830 --> 00:15:05.830
He and other Levites read aloud from the law of Moses.

00:15:05.830 --> 00:15:14.620
They not only read it, they explained it, putting meaning into it.

00:15:14.620 --> 00:15:19.620
As a people, we began to understand how badly we had disappointed Jehovah

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:26.019
by working on the Sabbath, offering lame sacrifices,

00:15:26.019 --> 00:15:30.019
and divorcing our wives to marry foreign women.

00:15:30.019 --> 00:15:33.019
It hurt our hearts.

00:15:33.019 --> 00:15:38.019
But by reading God's law, we were learning to beat Jehovah's people again.

00:15:38.019 --> 00:15:41.019
Do not mourn or weep.

00:15:41.019 --> 00:15:46.019
Now that you know what displeases God, you can do what pleases Him.

00:15:46.019 --> 00:15:48.019
So go.

00:15:48.019 --> 00:15:50.019
Eat the choice things.

00:15:50.019 --> 00:15:52.019
And drink what is sweet.

00:15:52.019 --> 00:15:55.019
And send portion to those who have nothing.

00:15:55.019 --> 00:15:57.019
And do not feel sad.

00:15:57.019 --> 00:16:01.019
For the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.

00:16:01.019 --> 00:16:12.190
We followed Jehovah's instructions to observe the festival of booths.

00:16:12.190 --> 00:16:34.090
We spent days rejoicing and giving thanks for Jehovah's blessing.

00:16:34.090 --> 00:16:43.799
Then on the 24th day, we assembled to read God's law, to confess our sins,

00:16:43.799 --> 00:16:45.799
and to weep over our wrongdoing.

00:16:45.799 --> 00:16:57.950
We made a binding agreement in writing.

00:16:57.950 --> 00:17:24.890
We resolved to obey Jehovah's law.

00:17:24.890 --> 00:17:26.890
Some soon forgot their promise.

00:17:26.890 --> 00:17:35.470
Pilate.

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:36.470
Who's our renterman?

00:17:36.470 --> 00:17:39.470
Put him in a bag, baskets hard to carry.

00:17:39.470 --> 00:17:45.990
You hear about Nehemiah's latest idea?

00:17:45.990 --> 00:17:48.990
I mean a plan to repopulate Jerusalem?

00:17:48.990 --> 00:17:51.990
I mean this ridiculous proposal, the force families to move into the city,

00:17:51.990 --> 00:17:53.990
one out of ten by lot.

00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:56.910
Yes, I heard.

00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:58.910
And I had to be one who was chosen.

00:17:58.910 --> 00:18:00.910
Why me?

00:18:00.910 --> 00:18:03.910
Does he care what this does to landholders like me?

00:18:04.910 --> 00:18:10.289
Oh, so why are you supposed to move?

00:18:10.289 --> 00:18:11.289
Move?

00:18:11.289 --> 00:18:12.289
I'm not moving anywhere.

00:18:12.289 --> 00:18:16.289
I have a right to live where I choose, and so do you.

00:18:16.289 --> 00:18:17.289
I wasn't selected.

00:18:17.289 --> 00:18:18.289
Not yet, you mean.

00:18:18.289 --> 00:18:25.099
And when you are, I need you to join me in refusing to move.

00:18:25.099 --> 00:18:31.180
Rayham, the king sent Nehemiah here to rebuild the city.

00:18:31.180 --> 00:18:35.299
Nehemiah is the governor.

00:18:35.299 --> 00:18:37.299
Governors come, governors go.

00:18:37.299 --> 00:18:40.299
The king is waiting for Nehemiah to return, and when he does,

00:18:40.299 --> 00:18:42.299
things will get back to normal.

00:18:42.299 --> 00:18:46.299
Even when Nehemiah goes back, Jehovah will still be here.

00:18:46.299 --> 00:18:49.299
It is his will that Jerusalem be rebuilt.

00:18:49.299 --> 00:18:52.609
Don't you believe that?

00:18:52.609 --> 00:18:55.609
So you will go along, Nehemiah.

00:18:55.609 --> 00:18:57.609
How can you be so ungrateful?

00:18:57.609 --> 00:19:05.819
Rayham, you're right.

00:19:05.819 --> 00:19:20.140
What was that all about?

00:19:20.140 --> 00:19:22.140
Rayham refuses to move into Jerusalem.

00:19:22.140 --> 00:19:28.680
He wants us to support him.

00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:32.440
What did you say?

00:19:32.440 --> 00:19:35.440
I told him Nehemiah is doing job as well.

00:19:35.440 --> 00:19:39.910
Rayham doesn't understand how happy he could be.

00:19:39.910 --> 00:19:45.920
He would just follow Jehovah's direction.

00:19:45.920 --> 00:19:48.920
So we will move if we're selected.

00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:51.299
Yes.

00:19:51.299 --> 00:19:56.380
I'd rather be like Nehemiah.

00:19:56.380 --> 00:19:58.380
And like Rayham.

00:19:58.380 --> 00:19:59.380
Do you agree?

00:19:59.380 --> 00:20:00.380
Yes.

00:20:00.380 --> 00:20:02.380
I'll meet you.

00:20:02.380 --> 00:20:13.089
At the inauguration of the walls,

00:20:13.089 --> 00:20:23.589
we filled Jerusalem with songs of praise and thanksgiving to God.

00:20:23.589 --> 00:20:30.529
Our great joy could be heard from far away.

00:20:30.529 --> 00:20:32.529
When I finally returned to the king,

00:20:32.529 --> 00:20:35.529
I thought about that day often.

00:20:35.529 --> 00:20:53.029
With what I know now, I wish I had never left.

00:20:53.029 --> 00:20:55.029
Jehovah raised up a messenger

00:20:55.029 --> 00:20:59.029
who chronicled the themes that happened in Jerusalem during my absence.

00:20:59.029 --> 00:21:02.410
His name was Malachi.

00:21:02.410 --> 00:21:09.759
Tobiah, despite not being a Jew,

00:21:09.759 --> 00:21:12.759
still found his way into the temple.

00:21:12.759 --> 00:21:20.190
He utilized his Jewish family ties to take advantage of the other Jews.

00:21:20.190 --> 00:21:22.190
What brings you to the temple?

00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:23.190
It's ten some time.

00:21:23.190 --> 00:21:25.190
I just wanted to see you.

00:21:25.190 --> 00:21:30.190
Oh, and to bring you this small gift.

00:21:30.190 --> 00:21:33.190
Tobiah, you're always so generous.

00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:36.190
It's nothing really.

00:21:36.190 --> 00:21:38.190
Is there nothing I can do for you?

00:21:38.190 --> 00:21:40.190
Well, since you asked.

00:21:40.190 --> 00:21:42.190
There's one little thing you can do.

00:21:42.190 --> 00:21:44.190
Tell me, what can I do for you?

00:21:44.190 --> 00:21:47.190
Well, speaking of family.

00:21:47.190 --> 00:21:50.190
When our relatives, here's a mine, I mean.

00:21:50.190 --> 00:21:52.190
Visit from Samaria.

00:21:52.190 --> 00:21:55.190
It would be so nice to have a place to eat with them.

00:21:55.190 --> 00:21:58.190
You know, right here in the temple, that is.

00:21:58.190 --> 00:22:01.190
After all, they worship Jehovah too.

00:22:01.190 --> 00:22:03.190
Often.

00:22:03.190 --> 00:22:06.190
Okay, well, sometimes.

00:22:06.190 --> 00:22:08.190
A room in the temple?

00:22:08.190 --> 00:22:10.190
But you know, I can't do that.

00:22:10.190 --> 00:22:14.789
That is all the rooms are in use.

00:22:14.789 --> 00:22:16.789
All of them.

00:22:16.789 --> 00:22:18.789
Aren't some of them just storerooms?

00:22:18.789 --> 00:22:23.039
But those are provisions for the Levites.

00:22:23.039 --> 00:22:25.039
But can't you clear one out for me?

00:22:25.039 --> 00:22:26.039
Just one.

00:22:26.039 --> 00:22:28.039
I only need one.

00:22:28.039 --> 00:22:31.039
But what will Nehemiah say?

00:22:31.039 --> 00:22:34.039
What differences it make?

00:22:34.039 --> 00:22:37.039
Nehemiah's far away in Shushan.

00:22:37.039 --> 00:22:39.039
But what if he finds out?

00:22:39.039 --> 00:22:41.039
Who is going to tell him?

00:22:41.039 --> 00:22:42.039
Are you going to tell him?

00:22:42.039 --> 00:22:43.039
No, no.

00:22:43.039 --> 00:22:45.039
Then, I worry.

00:22:45.039 --> 00:23:01.450
So once again, our high priest has given in to Tobiah.

00:23:01.450 --> 00:23:05.140
Where should I put this grade?

00:23:05.140 --> 00:23:06.140
There's room here.

00:23:06.140 --> 00:23:07.140
Be careful.

00:23:07.140 --> 00:23:10.960
I've got it.

00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:11.960
Look who's coming.

00:23:11.960 --> 00:23:18.140
Can you hurry, please?

00:23:18.140 --> 00:23:20.140
Once they get out of our way.

00:23:20.140 --> 00:23:23.140
Let's, uh, let's set the table here.

00:23:23.140 --> 00:23:26.140
And then the chairs come along the wall.

00:23:26.140 --> 00:23:28.140
Tobiah, tell me, please.

00:23:28.140 --> 00:23:30.140
Where should we store provisions now?

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:31.140
Wherever you want.

00:23:31.140 --> 00:23:33.140
That's your problem.

00:23:33.140 --> 00:23:35.140
And move along.

00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:37.140
Like now, please.

00:23:38.140 --> 00:23:44.900
All right, so.

00:23:44.900 --> 00:23:47.900
How could Eliashim let anyone?

00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:51.900
Let a lone man like Tobiah take over a room for his own use?

00:23:51.900 --> 00:23:56.900
After all that Nehemiah did to preserve the sacredness of the temple.

00:23:56.900 --> 00:23:59.900
Most people don't get the ties anymore anyway.

00:23:59.900 --> 00:24:02.900
If we want to eat, we need to go tend our own flocks in the fields.

00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:05.900
It's of no value to serve God.

00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:08.900
Wait, brothers.

00:24:08.900 --> 00:24:11.900
We can't let their wrong acts take away our joy.

00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:12.900
Why not?

00:24:12.900 --> 00:24:14.900
How have we benefited from serving Jehovah?

00:24:14.900 --> 00:24:15.900
Yes.

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:21.920
And does in the scriptures say, take good care of your sheep?

00:24:21.920 --> 00:24:25.920
It also says, a faithful man will receive many blessings.

00:24:25.920 --> 00:24:27.920
We must wait on Jehovah.

00:24:27.920 --> 00:24:33.900
In time, he will straighten everything out.

00:24:33.900 --> 00:24:37.900
Malakai saw how far the people had fallen.

00:24:37.900 --> 00:24:41.900
The Levites, once the proud keepers of Jehovah's standards,

00:24:41.900 --> 00:24:45.900
now found themselves questioning the value of their own service.

00:24:45.900 --> 00:25:18.099
Young man, I'll offer a sheep.

00:25:18.099 --> 00:25:23.380
The bigger the offering, the bigger the blessings.

00:25:23.380 --> 00:25:27.380
And besides, you know it's more impressive to the neighbors, huh?

00:25:27.380 --> 00:25:30.039
Thank you.

00:25:30.039 --> 00:25:31.039
I already have an offer.

00:25:31.039 --> 00:25:32.039
Yes, yes.

00:25:32.039 --> 00:25:36.039
But look, you seem like a nice man.

00:25:36.039 --> 00:25:39.039
So today for you, a special price, huh?

00:25:39.039 --> 00:25:41.039
Hardly more than you paid for these duffs.

00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:42.039
Come take a look.

00:25:42.039 --> 00:25:45.990
That sheep is blind.

00:25:45.990 --> 00:25:47.990
And look at how it works.

00:25:47.990 --> 00:25:51.990
Young man, that's absolutely normal for this breed.

00:25:51.990 --> 00:25:55.990
God's law says not to offer blind, lame or sick animals.

00:25:55.990 --> 00:25:59.990
If ever I can afford to offer a sheep, it'll be a sound one.

00:25:59.990 --> 00:26:00.990
Don't waste your money.

00:26:00.990 --> 00:26:02.990
She's a fine sheep at a fine price.

00:26:02.990 --> 00:26:03.990
I have to go.

00:26:03.990 --> 00:26:04.990
Be practical.

00:26:04.990 --> 00:26:11.579
Besides, it's only a tradition.

00:26:11.579 --> 00:26:14.579
Temple services are not the same.

00:26:14.579 --> 00:26:22.250
It's as if they don't even think about your home.

00:26:22.250 --> 00:26:25.250
Zuba, what's wrong?

00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:28.849
Zuba, what happened?

00:26:28.849 --> 00:26:32.859
How's Reham?

00:26:32.859 --> 00:26:43.299
Certificate of divorce.

00:26:43.299 --> 00:26:50.440
I tried to be a good wife, but it wasn't enough.

00:26:50.440 --> 00:26:56.150
Reham sent me away.

00:26:56.150 --> 00:26:58.150
Don't fear Zuba.

00:26:58.150 --> 00:27:01.150
You can live here with us.

00:27:01.150 --> 00:27:03.150
We can all share.

00:27:03.150 --> 00:27:06.940
It's all my fault.

00:27:06.940 --> 00:27:08.940
You mustn't think that way.

00:27:08.940 --> 00:27:11.940
But I didn't give him children.

00:27:11.940 --> 00:27:16.940
With or without children, marriage is sacred.

00:27:16.940 --> 00:27:58.220
Trust in Jehovah, he will never send you away.

00:27:58.220 --> 00:28:02.460
We had a visitor last night.

00:28:02.460 --> 00:28:03.460
It was your wife.

00:28:03.460 --> 00:28:08.700
Or should I say your former wife?

00:28:08.700 --> 00:28:15.069
Reham, don't you care how you've hurt your innocent mate?

00:28:15.069 --> 00:28:17.069
How can you be so hard-hearted?

00:28:17.069 --> 00:28:20.069
Look, Moses said if you find something indecent with your wife,

00:28:20.069 --> 00:28:22.069
a man must write a certificate of divorce,

00:28:22.069 --> 00:28:24.069
hand it to her, and dismiss her.

00:28:24.069 --> 00:28:28.069
If giving me no children is an indecent, then what is?

00:28:28.069 --> 00:28:30.069
Besides, I'm tired of living with her.

00:28:30.069 --> 00:28:32.069
I'm marrying Gisla today.

00:28:32.069 --> 00:28:34.069
Gisla.

00:28:34.069 --> 00:28:37.069
That mobile girl?

00:28:37.069 --> 00:28:41.069
I heard you bind yourself with an oath and a curse not to take away from the nations.

00:28:41.069 --> 00:28:45.069
God's law says they will turn your sons away from following me

00:28:45.069 --> 00:28:46.069
to serve other gods.

00:28:46.069 --> 00:28:49.069
Then Jehovah's anger will blaze against you.

00:28:49.069 --> 00:28:51.069
Who are you to counsel me?

00:28:51.069 --> 00:28:55.069
Every man must find his own joy and I intend to find mine.

00:28:55.069 --> 00:28:59.069
Reham, only Jehovah can give true joy.

00:28:59.069 --> 00:29:03.069
Do you really think you can give yourself more joy than he can?

00:29:03.069 --> 00:29:32.150
Jehovah, why do we treat each other so treacherously, profaning your covenant?

00:29:32.150 --> 00:29:50.940
Malachi, say to the priests who are despising my name.

00:29:51.940 --> 00:29:55.940
A son honors a father and a servant his master.

00:29:55.940 --> 00:30:01.940
So if I am a father, where is the honor do me?

00:30:01.940 --> 00:30:05.940
And if I am a master, where is the fear do me?

00:30:05.940 --> 00:30:18.630
My good man.

00:30:18.630 --> 00:30:21.099
My good man.

00:30:21.099 --> 00:30:47.779
We see you have no offering to you.

00:30:47.779 --> 00:30:49.779
Why have you, Levites, despised Jehovah's name?

00:30:49.779 --> 00:30:51.779
despised it.

00:30:51.779 --> 00:30:53.779
How?

00:30:53.779 --> 00:30:59.779
You present a blind, lame or sick animal as a sacrifice and say that it is nothing bad.

00:30:59.779 --> 00:31:01.779
Should Jehovah accept it from your hand?

00:31:01.779 --> 00:31:03.779
What's the meat is in our pot?

00:31:03.779 --> 00:31:05.779
No one can tell if it was lame or sound.

00:31:05.779 --> 00:31:07.779
What about Jehovah?

00:31:07.779 --> 00:31:09.779
Can he tell the difference?

00:31:09.779 --> 00:31:12.779
One day, Jehovah will come to his temple.

00:31:12.779 --> 00:31:15.779
He will cleanse you sons of Levi by fire.

00:31:15.779 --> 00:31:17.779
Malachi, what's gotten into you?

00:31:17.779 --> 00:31:22.779
Why should you complain when everyone else approves?

00:31:22.779 --> 00:31:26.779
Oh, priests, if you refuse to take it to heart, says Jehovah,

00:31:26.779 --> 00:31:32.779
I will send on you the curse and I will turn your blessings into curses.

00:31:32.779 --> 00:31:38.779
Return to me and I will return to you, says Jehovah.

00:31:38.779 --> 00:31:40.779
How are we supposed to return?

00:31:40.779 --> 00:31:43.779
Will a mere human rob God?

00:31:43.779 --> 00:31:46.779
But you are robbing me, says Jehovah.

00:31:46.779 --> 00:31:51.779
How have we robbed him in the tithes and in the contributions you are robbing me?

00:31:51.779 --> 00:31:56.779
Yes, the entire nation is, says Jehovah, bring the entire tithe into the storehouse.

00:31:56.779 --> 00:32:00.779
So there may be food in my house and test me out, please,

00:32:00.779 --> 00:32:03.779
and see whether I will not open to you the floodgates of the heavens

00:32:03.779 --> 00:32:07.779
and pour out on you a blessing until there is nothing lacking.

00:32:07.779 --> 00:32:13.660
And there's another thing you do so that he no longer looks favorably on anything you offer.

00:32:13.660 --> 00:32:15.660
Why not?

00:32:15.660 --> 00:32:18.660
Because you betray the wife of your youth.

00:32:18.660 --> 00:32:21.660
Although she's your partner, your legal wife,

00:32:21.660 --> 00:32:26.660
there are some who don't do that because they have what remains of the spirit.

00:32:26.660 --> 00:32:29.660
So guard yourselves respecting your spirit.

00:32:29.660 --> 00:32:34.460
Do not deal treacherously with the wife of your youth.

00:32:34.460 --> 00:32:39.460
For I hate divorce, says Jehovah, the God of Israel.

00:32:39.460 --> 00:32:42.460
The lips of a priest should safeguard knowledge

00:32:42.460 --> 00:32:45.460
and people should seek the law from his mouth.

00:32:45.460 --> 00:32:49.460
But you, you have made many stumble.

00:32:49.460 --> 00:33:02.059
Jehovah's message revealed the problem was in their hearts.

00:33:02.059 --> 00:33:10.109
In spite of that, Malachi sought out those who found joy in doing what was right.

00:33:10.109 --> 00:33:24.599
Pilate, how are you?

00:33:24.599 --> 00:33:27.599
Azuba, don't despair.

00:33:27.599 --> 00:33:32.599
You will see the distinction between the righteous and the wicked.

00:33:32.599 --> 00:33:36.599
Between one who serves God and one who doesn't.

00:33:36.599 --> 00:33:38.599
You must be a prophet.

00:33:38.599 --> 00:33:40.599
I serve Jehovah as you do.

00:33:40.599 --> 00:33:44.599
And I can tell you that when you speak with one another about Jehovah,

00:33:44.599 --> 00:33:47.599
he pays attention.

00:33:47.599 --> 00:33:50.599
A book is written before him of those who fear him

00:33:50.599 --> 00:33:56.220
and meditate on his name.

00:33:56.220 --> 00:34:12.619
