What have you been doing?

00:36:22.340 --> 00:36:25.340
Why have you in the deputy rulers neglected the House of God?

00:36:25.340 --> 00:36:30.340
You and they please cleanse this room and replace the utensils.

00:36:30.340 --> 00:36:31.340
Yes, ma'am.

00:36:31.340 --> 00:36:34.340
And gather all the Levites, the singers, the deputy rulers to me.

00:36:34.340 --> 00:36:36.340
I'm assigning them all back to their posts.

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:41.340
Padaya, I'm placing you, Shalomai, and Zadok in charge of the storeroom.

00:36:41.340 --> 00:36:42.340
Hainan will be your assistant.

00:36:42.340 --> 00:36:45.340
It's your responsibility to distribute provisions to your brothers.

00:36:45.340 --> 00:36:46.340
Yes, ma'am.

00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:48.340
Wait a second.

00:36:48.340 --> 00:36:49.340
Let me explain.

00:36:49.340 --> 00:36:53.340
I will tell all Judah to bring in the tent of the grain,

00:36:53.340 --> 00:36:56.340
the new wine, and the oil.

00:36:56.340 --> 00:36:59.340
I can expose.

00:36:59.340 --> 00:37:01.340
No, no way.

00:37:01.340 --> 00:37:16.090
Do remember me, oh my God.

00:37:16.090 --> 00:37:21.090
Do not wipe out my acts of loyal love for the House of my God.

00:37:21.090 --> 00:37:30.590
Not only have they neglected Jehovah's House,

00:37:30.590 --> 00:37:33.590
some of the Jews continued to conduct business on the Sabbath.

00:37:33.590 --> 00:37:38.260
A day Jehovah had declared as holy.

00:37:38.260 --> 00:37:43.260
What are you selling today?

00:37:43.260 --> 00:37:48.260
Only the best quality fish from tired.

00:37:48.260 --> 00:37:49.260
What are you doing?

00:37:49.260 --> 00:37:51.260
Do you not care that this is the Sabbath?

00:37:51.260 --> 00:37:53.260
Nehemiah.

00:37:53.260 --> 00:37:58.750
What is this evil thing you're doing?

00:37:58.750 --> 00:38:00.750
That's why God brought disaster on the city.

00:38:00.750 --> 00:38:02.750
People think it's acceptable now.

00:38:02.750 --> 00:38:05.750
What does Jehovah think?

00:38:05.750 --> 00:38:09.750
I stopped the buying and selling and ordered the doors closed

00:38:09.750 --> 00:38:20.469
so as to keep the Sabbath day holy.

00:38:20.469 --> 00:38:26.199
But the following week, the merchants try it again.

00:38:26.199 --> 00:38:28.199
What's the meaning of this?

00:38:28.199 --> 00:38:30.199
I had to sleep on the ground last night.

00:38:30.199 --> 00:38:32.199
You know God's law.

00:38:32.199 --> 00:38:33.199
No work.

00:38:33.199 --> 00:38:34.199
No business.

00:38:34.199 --> 00:38:36.199
On the Sabbath.

00:38:36.199 --> 00:38:37.199
Go.

00:38:37.199 --> 00:38:40.199
You know the Levites guard the gates and keep the Sabbath holy.

00:38:40.199 --> 00:38:42.199
Don't let anyone in.

00:38:42.199 --> 00:38:52.739
This too.

00:38:52.739 --> 00:38:55.739
Remember to my credit, oh my God.

00:38:55.739 --> 00:38:59.739
And show me pity according to your abundant loyal love.

00:38:59.739 --> 00:39:07.099
There was another thing that I had to do.

00:39:07.099 --> 00:39:12.360
Come back here.

00:39:12.360 --> 00:39:15.360
You have to listen to me. I'm your father.

00:39:15.360 --> 00:39:17.360
What's wrong with your children?

00:39:17.360 --> 00:39:20.360
They don't like coming to the temple.

00:39:20.360 --> 00:39:22.360
Oh, sweetie.

00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.360
Why don't you like it?

00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:26.360
So who gets it?

00:39:26.360 --> 00:39:32.329
Come back here now.

00:39:32.329 --> 00:39:33.329
I'm sorry, my lord.

00:39:33.329 --> 00:39:35.329
My wife speaks very little Hebrew.

00:39:35.329 --> 00:39:38.800
Did you not swear?

00:39:38.800 --> 00:39:41.800
Never to marry someone who doesn't serve Jehovah?

00:39:41.800 --> 00:39:43.800
My God, nobody cares.

00:39:43.800 --> 00:39:45.800
Did you not?

00:39:45.800 --> 00:39:46.800
Yes.

00:39:46.800 --> 00:39:47.800
Yes.

00:39:47.800 --> 00:39:49.800
Why have you ignored the command of Jehovah?

00:39:49.800 --> 00:39:51.800
And you're a whole no.

00:39:51.800 --> 00:39:52.800
Let me go.

00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:55.800
No wonder your children don't love Jehovah.

00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:59.800
Did you imagine that you could succeed without Jehovah's blessing?

00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:01.800
I prayed for Jehovah's blessing.

00:40:01.800 --> 00:40:02.800
Did you?

00:40:02.800 --> 00:40:04.800
But you didn't obey him.

00:40:04.800 --> 00:40:05.800
Rahim.

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:12.360
How can Jehovah bless something that is against his will?

00:40:12.360 --> 00:40:14.360
I was I surprised.

00:40:14.360 --> 00:40:18.360
The people were just following the bad example of those taking the lead.

00:40:18.360 --> 00:40:22.360
Eliaship's grandson married to Horonite.

00:40:22.360 --> 00:40:33.989
The daughter of Sin Ballet.

00:40:33.989 --> 00:40:38.340
Have you no respect for God's law?

00:40:38.340 --> 00:40:40.340
You should not give your daughters their sons.

00:40:40.340 --> 00:40:44.340
Nor accept any of their daughters for your sons.

00:40:44.340 --> 00:40:47.840
Or yourselves.

00:40:47.840 --> 00:40:53.690
Was it not because of these that King Solomon sinned?

00:40:53.690 --> 00:40:55.690
Grandfather, say something.

00:40:55.690 --> 00:40:56.690
Be still in my son.

00:40:56.690 --> 00:41:02.690
Is it not something unheard of for you to commit this great evil by marrying foreign women?

00:41:02.690 --> 00:41:11.320
You have to file the priesthood.

00:41:11.320 --> 00:41:13.320
You may not serve as a priest.

00:41:13.320 --> 00:41:15.320
Nor remain in Jerusalem.

00:41:15.320 --> 00:41:21.670
Fine.

00:41:21.670 --> 00:41:23.670
I'll go to Samaria.

00:41:23.670 --> 00:41:25.670
They're more tolerant there.

00:41:25.670 --> 00:41:32.449
But he's my grandson.

00:41:32.449 --> 00:41:37.860
Then why did you allow him to disregard Jehovah's laws?

00:41:37.860 --> 00:41:39.860
You know.

00:41:39.860 --> 00:41:44.860
Our temple services are what preserves our relationship with God.

00:41:44.860 --> 00:41:47.860
But as soon as I left,

00:41:47.860 --> 00:41:52.619
all of you, you let it fall apart.

00:41:52.619 --> 00:42:06.070
It took some time,

00:42:06.070 --> 00:42:10.070
but true worship was restored.

00:42:10.070 --> 00:42:31.989
When I look back on all that Jehovah enabled us to do,

00:42:31.989 --> 00:42:34.989
despite the opposition we faced,

00:42:34.989 --> 00:42:39.989
I recommend we turn the accusation of this edition against Nehemiah.

00:42:39.989 --> 00:42:43.989
Next sound they hear will be our battle cry.

00:42:43.989 --> 00:42:46.989
Are you gonna wait until they start killing us?

00:42:46.989 --> 00:42:48.989
The bad influences we avoided.

00:42:48.989 --> 00:42:51.989
I have a right to live where I choose, and so do you.

00:42:51.989 --> 00:42:53.989
I need you to join me in refusing to move.

00:42:53.989 --> 00:42:55.989
Don't waste your money. Be practical.

00:42:55.989 --> 00:42:57.989
Besides, it's only a tradition.

00:42:57.989 --> 00:43:01.989
If we want to eat, we need to attend our own flocks and fields.

00:43:01.989 --> 00:43:03.989
It's of no value to serve God.

00:43:03.989 --> 00:43:05.989
The sleepless nights.

00:43:05.989 --> 00:43:08.989
We must go to Jerusalem to keep an eye on Nehemiah.

00:43:08.989 --> 00:43:10.989
Don't you see these people hate what we're doing?

00:43:10.989 --> 00:43:11.989
They hate us.

00:43:11.989 --> 00:43:14.989
They have to live and work around them like we do.

00:43:14.989 --> 00:43:16.989
The sweat and toil.

00:43:16.989 --> 00:43:18.989
Besides, this work is too much for us.

00:43:18.989 --> 00:43:21.989
We're worn out. Why do we need a wall anyway?

00:43:21.989 --> 00:43:24.989
I just remember the joy we felt.

00:43:24.989 --> 00:43:29.369
Because we were serving Jehovah the right way.

00:43:29.369 --> 00:43:34.289
We thought we were just working on a wall.

00:43:34.289 --> 00:43:47.659
Jehovah was rebuilding our faith.

00:43:47.659 --> 00:43:50.659
I'll never forget how Jehovah brought us together

00:43:50.659 --> 00:43:52.659
to accomplish his will.

00:43:52.659 --> 00:43:57.019
He taught us to rely on him.

00:43:57.019 --> 00:44:02.159
He strengthened us.

00:44:02.159 --> 00:44:04.159
Eat the choice things.

00:44:04.159 --> 00:44:06.159
And drink what is sweet.

00:44:06.159 --> 00:44:08.159
And send portion to those who have nothing.

00:44:08.159 --> 00:44:10.159
And do not feel sad.

00:44:10.159 --> 00:44:14.159
For the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.

00:44:14.159 --> 00:44:26.780
Do remember me favorably.

00:44:26.780 --> 00:44:28.780
Oh my God.

00:44:28.780 --> 00:44:43.579
Nehemiah was a man of courage.

00:44:43.579 --> 00:44:47.579
He could have stayed in the luxurious palace of Shushan

00:44:47.579 --> 00:44:49.579
and served Jehovah from there.

00:44:49.579 --> 00:44:51.579
But he didn't.

00:44:51.579 --> 00:44:55.579
When Anita rose, he was ready to make the long journey

00:44:55.579 --> 00:44:59.579
to Jerusalem to support his brothers.

00:44:59.579 --> 00:45:01.579
But it wouldn't be easy.

00:45:01.579 --> 00:45:05.579
First he had to ask the king of Persia to let him go.

00:45:05.579 --> 00:45:09.579
What helped Nehemiah to be a courageous person for Jehovah?

00:45:09.579 --> 00:45:14.579
Did he rely on his personality or his good record with the king?

00:45:14.579 --> 00:45:16.579
Let's watch this part again.

00:45:16.579 --> 00:45:22.019
The place where my forefathers are buried lies in ruins.

00:45:22.019 --> 00:45:24.019
And its gates have been consumed by fire.

00:45:24.019 --> 00:45:26.019
Nehemiah, what is this?

00:45:26.019 --> 00:45:28.019
Speak frankly, what are you seeking?

00:45:28.019 --> 00:45:33.719
At once I prayed to the God of the heavens.

00:45:33.719 --> 00:45:38.949
If it pleases the king.

00:45:38.949 --> 00:45:42.949
And if your servant has found favor with you.

00:45:42.949 --> 00:45:48.940
Send me to Judah to the city where my forefathers are buried.

00:45:48.940 --> 00:45:50.940
And let me rebuild it.

00:45:50.940 --> 00:45:59.369
You may go.

00:45:59.369 --> 00:46:01.369
Jehovah was with us.

00:46:01.369 --> 00:46:08.860
Nehemiah immediately and humbly prayed to Jehovah.

00:46:08.860 --> 00:46:10.860
The true source of courage.

00:46:10.860 --> 00:46:14.860
In fact, he prayed repeatedly throughout his assignment.

00:46:14.860 --> 00:46:18.860
And Jehovah blessed his efforts.

00:46:18.860 --> 00:46:22.860
So lesson number one for us today.

00:46:22.860 --> 00:46:26.860
When times are hard, we may be quick to lean on Jehovah.

00:46:26.860 --> 00:46:28.860
But what if things are going well?

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:32.860
Are we still reliant on Jehovah?

00:46:32.860 --> 00:46:36.860
Or might we find ourselves becoming complacent?

00:46:36.860 --> 00:46:40.860
Perhaps even saying things are good in my life now.

00:46:40.860 --> 00:46:44.860
I know there's a need to get to work.

00:46:44.860 --> 00:46:48.860
But I've been serving Jehovah for many years now.

00:46:48.860 --> 00:46:50.860
I've done my part.

00:46:50.860 --> 00:46:52.860
Let someone else do it.

00:46:52.860 --> 00:46:56.860
Will Jehovah bless such an attitude?

00:46:56.860 --> 00:47:00.860
Wouldn't it be better to turn to Jehovah in prayer?

00:47:00.860 --> 00:47:06.860
Asking him to give you the courage and joy to continue to reach out

00:47:06.860 --> 00:47:08.860
in your service to him?

00:47:08.860 --> 00:47:16.860
You just might be surprised at the door Jehovah opens for you.

00:47:16.860 --> 00:47:22.860
Now, once Nehemiah arrived in Jerusalem, he didn't just give orders, did he?

00:47:22.860 --> 00:47:28.860
The Bible says that he daily worked alongside his fellow Israelites

00:47:28.860 --> 00:47:32.860
from the break of dawn until the stars came out.

00:47:32.860 --> 00:47:37.860
In a similar way, when we show a self-sacrificing spirit,

00:47:37.860 --> 00:47:43.860
Jehovah will give us the energy needed to carry out the task at hand.

00:47:43.860 --> 00:47:49.860
The Israelites completed the wall building project in just 52 days.

00:47:49.860 --> 00:47:57.860
What an amazing feat, especially in the face of continual opposition.

00:47:57.860 --> 00:48:01.860
At first, it came in the form of mocking.

00:48:01.860 --> 00:48:05.860
Then the opposers threatened to attack.

00:48:05.860 --> 00:48:09.860
There were Samaritans in the North, Ammonites in East,

00:48:09.860 --> 00:48:14.860
Arabs in the South, and Ashtadites in the West.

00:48:14.860 --> 00:48:18.860
Jerusalem was surrounded by enemies.

00:48:18.860 --> 00:48:22.860
It could have been easy to feel trapped and to give in to fear.

00:48:22.860 --> 00:48:24.860
What did Nehemiah do?

00:48:24.860 --> 00:48:27.860
Well, what was his pattern?

00:48:27.860 --> 00:48:29.860
In his own words, he says,

00:48:29.860 --> 00:48:33.860
we prayed to our God.

00:48:33.860 --> 00:48:37.860
Then Nehemiah strengthened the people by telling them

00:48:37.860 --> 00:48:41.860
do not be afraid of them.

00:48:41.860 --> 00:48:46.860
Remember Jehovah, who is great and awe-inspiring.

00:48:46.860 --> 00:48:49.860
And so they kept building.

00:48:49.860 --> 00:48:53.860
After Nehemiah's enemies realized that their open threats had failed,

00:48:53.860 --> 00:48:55.860
did they give up?

00:48:55.860 --> 00:48:56.860
No.

00:48:56.860 --> 00:49:00.860
They now turn to other forms of opposition.

00:49:00.860 --> 00:49:07.860
In fact, they tried three different schemes to sidetrack Nehemiah from the work.

00:49:07.860 --> 00:49:09.860
Did you notice them?

00:49:09.860 --> 00:49:11.860
Let's watch the video again.

00:49:11.860 --> 00:49:20.809
They asked to meet Nehemiah halfway.

00:49:20.809 --> 00:49:23.809
Tell this to Nehemiah.

00:49:23.809 --> 00:49:24.809
Come.

00:49:24.809 --> 00:49:29.809
And let us set a time to meet together in the valley plain of Ono.

00:49:29.809 --> 00:49:36.170
They're trying to lure me away from Jerusalem to do the harm.

00:49:36.170 --> 00:49:39.170
They spread false rumors.

00:49:39.170 --> 00:49:43.170
Geesham, it's time to implement your plan.

00:49:43.170 --> 00:49:47.170
Tobiah, write this down.

