And they used a traitor to try and trick Nehemiah.

00:50:07.860 --> 00:50:09.860
They're coming to kill you.

00:50:09.860 --> 00:50:14.860
By night, we must go into the temple and close the doors.

00:50:14.860 --> 00:50:17.860
Shemaah, should a man like me run away?

00:50:17.860 --> 00:50:19.860
You don't understand.

00:50:19.860 --> 00:50:22.860
What would that do to the spirit of the entire nation?

00:50:22.860 --> 00:50:24.860
It's the only safe place.

00:50:24.860 --> 00:50:27.860
Besides, I'm not a priest.

00:50:27.860 --> 00:50:30.860
If I entered the temple, that would be valid reason to kill me.

00:50:30.860 --> 00:50:33.860
I will not go in.

00:50:33.860 --> 00:50:35.860
That decision would be foolish, Nehemiah.

00:50:35.860 --> 00:50:44.389
Oh, I see.

00:50:44.389 --> 00:50:47.389
Tobiah and San Ballet put you up to this.

00:50:47.389 --> 00:50:49.389
Didn't they, you hypocrite?

00:50:49.389 --> 00:50:51.389
Made Jehovah remember them?

00:50:51.389 --> 00:50:55.389
And all of you false prophets who keep trying to frighten me.

00:50:55.389 --> 00:50:57.389
Come here, Nehemiah.

00:50:57.389 --> 00:50:58.389
We have work to do.

00:50:58.389 --> 00:51:04.739
Three schemes.

00:51:04.739 --> 00:51:06.739
Three failures.

00:51:06.739 --> 00:51:08.739
So lesson number two.

00:51:08.739 --> 00:51:17.739
Like Nehemiah, we might encounter opposers who scheme to bring our loyal service to a halt.

00:51:17.739 --> 00:51:21.739
Some may invite us to meet them halfway, so to speak.

00:51:21.739 --> 00:51:27.739
They may try to convince us that if we served Jehovah with just a little less zeal,

00:51:27.739 --> 00:51:32.739
we could pursue worldly goals at the same time.

00:51:32.739 --> 00:51:36.739
However, because God's kingdom comes first in our lives,

00:51:36.739 --> 00:51:40.739
we can be like Nehemiah and refuse to compromise.

00:51:40.739 --> 00:51:43.739
We know where this world's headed.

00:51:43.739 --> 00:51:49.599
Opposers also spread false accusations against us.

00:51:49.599 --> 00:51:54.599
In some lands, we're accused of posing a threat to the state.

00:51:54.599 --> 00:51:58.599
Some accusations have been successfully rebutted in court.

00:51:58.599 --> 00:52:06.599
But whatever the outcome, we're confident that Jehovah will direct matters according to his will.

00:52:06.599 --> 00:52:12.599
Opposition may also come from those who pretend to serve Jehovah.

00:52:12.599 --> 00:52:18.599
Just as a fellow Jew tried to get Nehemiah to break God's law to save his life,

00:52:18.599 --> 00:52:25.599
so former witnesses may try to get us to compromise in one way or another.

00:52:25.599 --> 00:52:31.599
However, we reject apostates because we know that our lives are saved,

00:52:31.599 --> 00:52:36.599
not by breaking God's laws, but by keeping them.

00:52:36.599 --> 00:52:42.599
Each time Nehemiah refused to fall into their trap, why?

00:52:42.599 --> 00:52:45.599
Because he had a brilliant mind? No.

00:52:45.599 --> 00:52:53.599
It was because he relied on Jehovah and Jehovah gave him the insight needed

00:52:53.599 --> 00:52:57.599
to see through their deceptions.

00:52:57.599 --> 00:53:01.599
After the walls built, Nehemiah left Jerusalem for a while.

00:53:01.599 --> 00:53:05.599
But what did he find on his return?

00:53:05.599 --> 00:53:12.599
Instead of coming back to find true worship thriving, he found it barely surviving.

00:53:12.599 --> 00:53:18.599
All the work that he had done to help the people to trust Jehovah.

00:53:18.599 --> 00:53:21.599
How do you think he felt?

00:53:21.599 --> 00:53:25.599
He could have said, that's it. I'm out.

00:53:25.599 --> 00:53:29.599
Let someone else clean this up and walk away.

00:53:29.599 --> 00:53:33.599
But did he? Let's watch again.

00:53:33.599 --> 00:53:36.599
Why have you and the deputy rulers neglected the House of God?

00:53:36.599 --> 00:53:39.599
You and they please cleanse this room.

00:53:39.599 --> 00:53:45.599
You know God's law. No work. No business on the Sabbath.

00:53:45.599 --> 00:53:47.599
Go!

00:53:47.599 --> 00:53:52.599
Did you not swear? Never to marry someone who doesn't serve Jehovah?

00:53:52.599 --> 00:53:57.599
Then why have you ignored the command of Jehovah and your own oath?

00:53:57.599 --> 00:54:03.599
Also, the Liarship's grandson married a Hora Knight. The daughter of San Ballet.

00:54:03.599 --> 00:54:11.190
You should not give your daughters their sons, nor accept any of their daughters for your sons.

00:54:11.190 --> 00:54:18.190
You have to file the priesthood. You may not serve as a priest, nor remain in Jerusalem.

00:54:18.190 --> 00:54:24.190
It took some time, but true worship was restored.

00:54:24.190 --> 00:54:32.090
Nehemiah didn't walk away, did he?

00:54:32.090 --> 00:54:36.090
No, he persevered in his assignment. Why?

00:54:36.090 --> 00:54:40.090
Because he held on to his joy.

00:54:40.090 --> 00:54:46.090
You see, his main source of joy came not from his accomplishments,

00:54:46.090 --> 00:54:52.090
not from the security of walls, nor even from what others were doing.

00:54:52.090 --> 00:54:56.090
From where does true joy come?

00:54:56.090 --> 00:55:04.090
Nehemiah himself told us, the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.

00:55:04.090 --> 00:55:07.090
So here's lesson number three for us.

00:55:07.090 --> 00:55:16.090
Despite challenges and setbacks, we can be joyful because true joy comes from a good relationship with Jehovah.

00:55:16.090 --> 00:55:19.090
Nehemiah was a man like you and me.

00:55:19.090 --> 00:55:27.090
Remember, he didn't have Jehovah's power displayed supernaturally to him like Moses and Joshua did.

00:55:27.090 --> 00:55:29.090
But what did he have?

00:55:29.090 --> 00:55:33.090
He had prayer. He had faith.

00:55:33.090 --> 00:55:38.090
And he had trust. Those were his tools.

00:55:38.090 --> 00:55:45.090
And there's no doubt that Jehovah was active on behalf of Nehemiah, guiding and blessing his efforts.

00:55:46.090 --> 00:55:50.090
We have those same tools today.

00:55:50.090 --> 00:55:57.090
Pray to Jehovah, put faith in him, and trust that he will bless your self-sacrificing efforts.

00:55:57.090 --> 00:56:06.090
Just as Jehovah gave Nehemiah the courage, the energy, the insight, and the perseverance to carry out his assignment,

00:56:06.090 --> 00:56:09.090
he'll do the same for you.

00:56:11.849 --> 00:56:17.849
Like Nehemiah, we gain strength from our association with faithful fellow believers.

00:56:17.849 --> 00:56:24.849
Likewise, our next song draws attention to the blessings we enjoy as a united brotherhood.

